<subSubSection id="D7162C736B55E4976D55912A16BC2D46" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" type="comments">
<paragraph id="586E8A0D71752A6B15248B7E10D36CF2" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="892B4EEB1DA7A7C9018F57C954223D11" pageId="2" pageNumber="3">
Based on the principle of priority, 
<taxonomicName id="5877F4EE38905870892BF8280C89362A" class="Pucciniomycetes" genus="Hemileia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Hemileia deightonii" order="Pucciniales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="deightonii">Hemileia deightonii</taxonomicName>
is the correct name for this species. This name had been placed in 
<taxonomicName id="2C79E3693757CFD3B2FB37E7A394A8B5" class="Pucciniomycetes" genus="Uredo" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Uredo" order="Pucciniales" pageId="2" pageNumber="3" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">Uredo</taxonomicName>
because of the lack of teliospores as dictated by the ICBN in effect at that time but is now allowed by the ICN.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
